<section class="p-5">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="text-center fw-bold pb-4">
      The three pillars of the human language:
    </h2>
    <p class="text-center lead">
      Dive into these core topics in our Writing (blog) section. Discover how
      they inform our understanding, teaching, and joy of speaking.
    </p>
    <div class="row text-center g-4 fs-5 mt-2">
      <div class="col-md">
        <div class="card text-primary border border-primary">
          <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="h1 mb-3">
              <i class="bi bi-hourglass-split"></i>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title mb-3">Mythology</h3>
            <p class="lead">Why we speak in stories...</p>
            <div class="collapse" id="mythologyCollapse">
              <p class="card-text">
                From the gods of ancient Greece to creation tales around the
                globe, mythology reveals how we first used mythic narratives to
                explain our world and invented words to give those stories life.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary mt-4 toggle-btn"
              type="button"
              data-bs-toggle="collapse"
              data-bs-target="#mythologyCollapse"
              aria-expanded="false"
              aria-controls="mythologyCollapse"
            >
              Read More
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md">
        <div class="card bg-lightDark text-light">
          <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="h1 mb-3">
              <i class="bi bi-journal-bookmark"></i>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title mb-3">Literature</h3>
            <p class="lead">How we shape and share ideas...</p>
            <div class="collapse" id="literatureCollapse">
              <p class="card-text">
                Whether epic poetry, philosophical treatises or the latest
                novel, literature is the living archive of human thought. It
                refines our vocabulary, stretches our imagination, and passes
                culture down through the ages.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-dark mt-4 toggle-btn"
              type="button"
              data-bs-toggle="collapse"
              data-bs-target="#literatureCollapse"
              aria-expanded="false"
              aria-controls="literatureCollapse"
            >
              Read More
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md">
        <div class="card text-primary border border-primary">
          <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="h1 mb-3">
              <i class="bi bi-translate"></i>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title mb-3">Linguistics</h3>
            <p class="lead">What makes language tick...</p>
            <div class="collapse" id="linguisticsCollapse">
              <p class="card-text">
                Across time and technology, Linguistics reveals the hidden
                machinery of language, the scientific study of sounds,
                structures, and meaning that lets us reverse-engineer how words
                work to learn, teach, and innovate.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary mt-4 toggle-btn"
              type="button"
              data-bs-toggle="collapse"
              data-bs-target="#linguisticsCollapse"
              aria-expanded="false"
              aria-controls="linguisticsCollapse"
            >
              Read More
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const collapseButtons = document.querySelectorAll(".toggle-btn")

    collapseButtons.forEach((button) => {
      const collapse = document.querySelector(
        button.getAttribute("data-bs-target")
      )

      collapse.addEventListener("show.bs.collapse", () => {
        button.textContent = "Read Less"
      })

      collapse.addEventListener("hide.bs.collapse", () => {
        button.textContent = "Read More"
      })
    })
  })
</script>
